{"author":{"id":"f270607f232f5ea3e06daa2368d41de7674a6d0d64158946f2581dde2c4881fc"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1680780249,"nonce":"XgSCWTwJy4lsVzu5QXEO0swom8g=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5ZV5O4","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5233#issuecomment-1498911672"},"message":"Hard to diagnose this problem without having access to the machine where it occurs, but exit code 126 usually means \"command not executable\".\nmedaka is tool that's notoriously difficult to install with conda since the dependencies are hard to resolve and conda often gives up eventually. So it could be that your conda env doesn't have a successfully installed tool, which Galaxy only finds out at run time.\nHave you checked whether you can execute the tool from the command line? Or have you tried to conda list the contents of the env? If this is really a problem with the conda install, you may want to give mamba a try because it's much better and faster at resolving complex envs.","files":null}]}